## PART AC — AUDIO & MUSIC PROTOCOL

Voice is locked in Part K. This part covers everything else: music selection, sound design, ambient layers, SFX, silence, and how all audio elements coexist in the audio mix.

### AC.1 — THE PRINCIPLE

A reel's audio is half its impact. Most creators treat music as decoration; great creators treat audio as performance. Every reel has a deliberate audio architecture with stated decisions for each layer.

### AC.2 — THE FOUR AUDIO LAYERS

Every reel's audio is built from four stacked layers, each with declared levels:

LAYER 1 — VOICE / VO (if SPOKEN):
Already specified in Part K. -6dB intimate baseline.

LAYER 2 — MUSIC BED:
The track underneath everything. Genre, tempo, era, and mood all declared.

LAYER 3 — AMBIENT BED:
Environmental sound — room tone, traffic distant, birds, water, crowd-hum, cafe-buzz, rain, wind. Always present, always low.

LAYER 4 — SFX:
Specific sound effects — door click, fabric rustle, glass clink, footsteps, cap unscrewing, splash, breath, heartbeat. Punctuates beats.

### AC.3 — MUSIC SELECTION PROTOCOL

EVERY REEL DECLARES:

```
