### AC.4 — AUDIO MIX LEVELS (mandatory per reel)

Reference levels at full mix:

```
VO PEAK: -6 dB (intimate range)
MUSIC AT FULL:  -12 dB (during VO-LESS beats)
MUSIC DUCKED: -24 dB (during VO peaks)
AMBIENT BED: -24 to -30 dB (always present, never absent)
SFX HITS: -3 to -6 dB (punctuated, attention-grabbing)
SILENCE BEATS: declared explicitly per frame
```

Music NEVER masks voice. Voice NEVER drowns ambient. Ambient NEVER goes below threshold of audibility.

### AC.5 — SILENCE AS DIRECTIVE

Silent beats are the most powerful audio tool. Use them deliberately:

WHEN TO USE SILENCE:
- Hero visual frame (let image breathe)
- Emotional peak (silence amplifies feeling)
- Pre-payoff anticipation (build tension)
- Sign-off frame (visual seals it)
- Frame transitions (sudden cut to silence is a rhythm beat)

DECLARATION:
```
FRAME N: AUDIO SILENT (intentional)
- Music: hard cut at frame start, returns at frame N+1
- Ambient: cut to ambient-only, no music
- VO: SILENT
- SFX: optional single hit (footstep, door, breath) acceptable
```

### AC.6 — SFX VOCABULARY

Every reel declares which SFX punctuate which beats:

DIEGETIC (sounds the world makes):
- Footsteps on surface (heel click on marble, soft on wood, sand crunch)
- Fabric (silk slip rustle, leather creak, denim shift)
- Glass (clink, set-down, refraction-ting)
- Liquid (pour, splash, drop, swirl)
- Door (click, slam, creak, latch)
- Breath (inhale, exhale, sigh, sharp catch)
- Heartbeat (low pulse — tension)
- Lip (parting, smacking, breath release)
- Hair (brush stroke, comb pull, blow-dryer warm)
- Product (cap unscrew, atomizer spray, tube squeeze)

NON-DIEGETIC (sounds added for effect):
- Riser / build-up (anticipation)
- Drop / impact (payoff)
- Whoosh (transitions, motion accentuation)
- Reverse-cymbal swell (build to reveal)
- Sub-bass drop (electric hits)
- Sparkle / shimmer (magic moments)

### AC.7 — TRENDING AUDIO RULES

When using trending audio:

EXTRACT THE MECHANICS, NOT THE SURFACE (per Part T):
- Hook moment in trending track lands at X seconds
- Beat-drop or vocal-stab is the algorithmic favorite — align reel pivot to that moment
- Vocal lyrics must support visual or contrast meaningfully
- If lyrics dominate audio, frame pace must match phrase rhythm

ATTRIBUTION:
- Always credit trending audio in caption
- Use platform's official audio (not re-uploads)
- Audio drives discovery — choose with strategic eye toward trend lifecycle

NEVER:
- Use trending audio whose lyrics conflict with reel mood
- Choose audio just because it's trending without checking the visual fit
- Layer your own VO over a trending VOCAL (clashes audio)
- Use audio past its peak window (avoid week-old trends)

